OAS Chief Arrives in Hurricane-Hit Nicaragua
MANAGUA , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- Secretary General of the Organization of American States ( OAS ) Cesar Gaviria arrived here Saturday for a two-day visit to Nicaragua , one of the worst hit by Hurricane Mitch in the last week of October .
" What occurred with Hurricane Mitch , in terms of lost lives and damage to infrastructure , is terrible , " Gaviria said upon arrival at the Managua International Airport .
The OAS has contributed 70,000 U.S. dollars to assist Nicaraguan victims of the devastating storm , he noted .
The OAS chief is scheduled to meet with Nicaraguan President Arnoldo Aleman on Sunday , according to a press release issued by the Foreign Ministry .
